Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.01,0:01:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Finished!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.78,0:01:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! I’ve done it!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.92,0:01:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew! So fast!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.44,0:02:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! We’d better wrap this up quickly \Nor it’ll be tea-time.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.88,0:02:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how very pretty!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.37,0:02:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you throwing that away?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.40,0:02:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it’s only scraps.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.40,0:02:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What a waste. May I have it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.39,0:02:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Sure... Go ahead, it’s nothing much.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.84,0:02:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.28,0:02:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.55,0:02:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What a queer girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.16,0:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, who is she?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s the one who’s been \Nworking in the dining hall lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.13,0:02:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys, I think that's her name.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.09,0:02:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.24,0:02:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.91,0:02:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.56,0:03:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.71,0:03:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.02,0:03:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.63,0:03:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, bother!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.50,0:03:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we were about to go out.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.36,0:03:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do about it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.76,0:03:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so sorry, I’ll wash it straight away.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.80,0:03:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you'd better make sure it's real clean!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Come and take it from my room. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.04,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I am very sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.57,0:03:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch where you’re going next time! {lit: don't blank while you walk }
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.48,0:03:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Gladys?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.35,0:03:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not hurt, are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.58,0:03:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.31,0:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe her! It was Pam who wasn’t watching where she's going!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.30,0:03:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever shall I do? \NThis was meant for Headmistress and her visitor.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.09,0:03:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll fetch Pam's skirt for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.76,0:03:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.86,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind, off you go, quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.58,0:03:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, I’ll be back in a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.57,0:03:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks about our age, doesn’t she?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.54,0:03:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think so.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.44,0:04:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I’ll do it, sorry for the delay!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.77,0:04:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh! Your hands...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.92,0:04:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... They’re terrible, aren’t they? \NThey always get rough no matter what. {to become rough (of skin); to get chapped}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor thing, don’t they hurt?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.36,0:04:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t help it, washing hundreds of plates every day.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.26,0:04:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness... I know, Kathleen has some ointment for chapped hands. Wait here. {teare = rough hands; red hands}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.15,0:04:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew, thank God, \Nthe stain has come off.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.01,0:04:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This ointment works wonders.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.28,0:04:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve always had trouble with rough hands myself, \Nand my father sent me this from abroad.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.71,0:04:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. My father was a kind man too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.16,0:04:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Was?" Then...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.89,0:04:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he passed away three years ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.27,0:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... So that’s why you’re working \Ninstead of going to school?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.21,0:04:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’ve younger brothers and sisters, \Nso Mother and I must manage.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.86,0:04:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that must be hard on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.50,0:05:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all, I like working.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.10,0:05:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I must go now!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.27,0:05:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys, take this ointment.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.57,0:05:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it every time after washing \Nand your hands will soon be better.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.14,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.13,0:05:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... So that’s what it was.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.82,0:05:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.07,0:05:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d been wondering for a while, \Nand now I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.55,0:05:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a father, \Nit must be hard for that family.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.09,0:05:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys, with that slight little body, \Nis supporting them all.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.73,0:05:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How splendid of her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.16,0:05:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s quite different from us, \Nwho only need think of our studies.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.40,0:05:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys is a brave girl, working so hard \Nin spite of poverty and hardship.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.74,0:05:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, you do exaggerate.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.56,0:05:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I’m sure it’s so.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.88,0:05:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But she doesn’t look \Nall that miserable, does she? {/pathetic}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.35,0:05:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she’s so very cheerful.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.42,0:05:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what’s splendid about Gladys.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.75,0:05:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it, though?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.19,0:05:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it’s just Kathleen imagining it? {/convincing herself}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.23,0:06:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, you’re too much \Nof a young lady to understand. {probably means "you come from a good family"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.70,0:06:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.56,0:06:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If she really is in trouble, \NI’d like to help her somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.77,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.17,0:06:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a splendid play today. {??? }
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.54,0:06:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... If only it hadn’t been in French, I’d have understood it far better.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.76,0:06:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I did understand some of it. \N“Je t’aime” and “Adieu.”
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.75,0:06:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan! Even I knew that much.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.62,0:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But listen, did you notice?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.77,0:06:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle was in tears right through the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.09,0:06:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I saw it! She’s more of a romantic than we’d thought, and such a soft-hearted one too. {easily moved to tears; given to weeping; lachrymose}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.69,0:06:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that, you know. You needn’t have said “more than we’d thought.” {lit: ... was extra/unneeded}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.53,0:06:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What, what is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.49,0:06:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.54,0:06:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she running all the way to town?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.31,0:06:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She does it every day, you know. {lit: commuting by running}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.35,0:06:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.35,0:06:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, she must be saving her bus fare.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.54,0:06:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re joking!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.12,0:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s form a Gladys Support Club.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.56,0:07:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I want to help her, \Nworking so hard as she does.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.56,0:07:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I’m in. \NWhat shall we do, though?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.33,0:07:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How about giving her brothers some books?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.74,0:07:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’ve still got plenty I read when I was little.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.49,0:07:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give her some clothes, \Nthe sort in her size.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.51,0:07:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I’ll get Mother to send me \Nsome sweets to pass on.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.45,0:07:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Settled!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.61,0:07:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s begin at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.92,0:07:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But why give these things to me?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.99,0:07:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we want to support you, Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.20,0:07:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t we!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.86,0:07:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We do!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.50,0:07:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Watching you work so hard gives us courage too!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.17,0:07:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our way of saying thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.00,0:07:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d be glad to know \Nyou liked and accepted them. {lit: if you accepted them freely; readily; cheerfully; without any sense of hesitation; without reserve; without treating it as a big deal; casually, we'd be happy}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.84,0:07:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,May I really?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.89,0:07:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You may!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.46,0:07:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, then I will!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.21,0:08:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.98,0:08:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.65,0:08:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.25,0:08:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.87,0:08:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That was well done!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.15,0:08:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The first operation of the \NGladys Support Club was a success!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.36,0:08:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s carry it on!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.03,0:08:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.63,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait, just a moment!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.63,0:08:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.17,0:08:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.35,0:08:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it for your bus fare.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.16,0:08:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.78,0:08:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot take that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.61,0:08:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... With this rain, \Nthere can be no going to town.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.33,0:08:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? There’s Gladys.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.10,0:08:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s on the late shift today. {/afternoon shift}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.52,0:08:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! She’s soaking wet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.52,0:08:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t take the bus again.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.40,0:08:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I do hope she doesn’t catch cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.96,0:09:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go first! {???? maybe "saki ni"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.33,0:09:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.83,0:09:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so pale. \NAre you all right? {actually maybe not pale but red, lit is just "face color is bad"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.33,0:09:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’m fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.77,0:09:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then. Bye.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.56,0:09:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.30,0:09:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Matron, will Gladys be all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.56,0:09:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to worry, it’s only a mild cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.26,0:09:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She was already tired, \Nthen she went into the rain too.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.00,0:10:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave her my medicine, \Na little sleep will put her right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.17,0:10:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Matron.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.32,0:10:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I... gotta hurry...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.32,0:10:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s fretting about her work.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.18,0:10:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.68,0:10:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Come along.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.38,0:10:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.65,0:10:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m calling a meeting of the Gladys Support Club.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.45,0:10:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.72,0:10:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Two:
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.16,0:10:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll do Gladys’s work for her.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.90,0:10:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Put them on that counter.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.50,0:10:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi, we can stand in for her, \Nbut do you know how it’s done?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.44,0:10:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as they’re clean, \Nit doesn’t matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.52,0:10:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me, I’m an expert washer-up. {dishwasher}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.61,0:10:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll make them shine \Nand give Gladys a real surprise.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.84,0:11:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you think we’re terribly efficient?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.49,0:11:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, we’d make fine housewives one day.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.10,0:11:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But is this really the only drying cloth? {/dishcloth}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.97,0:11:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s sopping wet and won’t dry a thing. {when I worked as a waiter myself, finding a dry dishcloth was our #1 problem too, LMAO. nice to see not a thing had changed}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.17,0:11:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it a good wring-out, \Nthat should do i— Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.27,0:11:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.67,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.84,0:11:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right, missing one plate \Nwon’t make any difference.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.71,0:11:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I only hope Gladys doesn’t get scolded.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.43,0:11:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, that’s it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.27,0:11:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow’s Sunday, so Gladys has the day off.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.07,0:11:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole day’s rest will put her right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.18,0:11:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.08,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.48,0:11:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really better already?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.95,0:11:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to take it easy now. {lit: it's better not to force yourself}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.55,0:12:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Er... Is this...?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.46,0:12:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't they real clean? \NWe did it for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.04,0:12:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, hurry home and get some rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.43,0:12:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, think nothing of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.71,0:12:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That went well, didn’t it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.00,0:12:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I feel jolly pleased.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.23,0:12:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I appreciate it, but…
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.20,0:12:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Gladys?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.04,0:12:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.47,0:12:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you re-doing it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.98,0:13:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. \NI was touched by your kindness, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.88,0:13:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a set procedure, \Nand it has to be followed.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.78,0:13:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, the plates aren’t to be wiped at all, \Nonly scalded in boiling water and stacked in the rack.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.67,0:13:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other rules too…
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.52,0:13:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.56,0:13:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let me help.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.68,0:13:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, please. It’s past bedtime.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.66,0:13:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d best go back to your dormitory.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.15,0:13:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.03,0:13:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my job. \NI’m paid to do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.94,0:13:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we only gave you extra work?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.60,0:13:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. Thanks to you I feel better \Nand I’ll be finished sooner.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.28,0:13:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m grateful.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.78,0:13:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But please—don’t breathe \Na word of this to anyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.35,0:13:52.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will Gladys really run \Nall the way home this late?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.43,0:14:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.63,0:14:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.52,0:14:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys dropped this yesterday.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.40,0:14:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it to town for her, will you?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.54,0:14:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.14,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? How come? Good gracious!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.96,0:14:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what? \NGladys is entering the marathon?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.45,0:14:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. But unless this form is handed in \Nby 10:30, she can’t compete. {?? /half past ten}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.49,0:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But she had a fever yesterday—\Nshe can’t possibly run!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.48,0:14:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not all. In fact, last night...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.06,0:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.15,0:15:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They refused?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.65,0:15:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What bad luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.22,0:15:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're also not well today, \Nso let's pack it in. {??? lit: it can't be helped - not sure what she means, sounds like a non sequitur to me, like it already can't be helped, regardless of her health}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.66,0:15:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.33,0:15:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.10,0:15:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.50,0:15:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you still make it in time?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.08,0:15:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.05,0:15:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.72,0:15:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys still looks a bit pale.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.36,0:15:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she’s all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.66,0:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She was working late into the night.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.71,0:16:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.86,0:16:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She never tells anyone a word.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.37,0:16:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn’t we stop her?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.00,0:16:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Gladys must absolutely run today.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.64,0:16:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress? \NSo you knew about this all too?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.19,0:16:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. She’s a born runner.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.92,0:16:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s even talk of a scholarship.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.48,0:16:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But she chose to keep working while she runs, \Nso she runs to and from St. Clare’s every day.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.20,0:16:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so that's why...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.62,0:16:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She wasn’t just saving her bus fare?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.22,0:16:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is a special day.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.12,0:16:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If she finishes in the top three, \Nshe’ll qualify for a bigger competition.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.56,0:16:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if she shines there, \Nshe may be chosen as an Olympic hopeful. {/candidate}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.73,0:16:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Olympics?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.22,0:16:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.23,0:16:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys has staked everything on this race.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.72,0:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If it’s so important, she ought \Nto have taken a day off yesterday.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.91,0:16:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just what makes her so splendid.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.08,0:16:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.45,0:16:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.83,0:17:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is the moment \Nfor the Support Club to prove itself.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.10,0:17:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Let’s cheer her on with all we’ve got.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.19,0:17:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys, steady now!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.18,0:17:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.19,0:17:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight, fight!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.18,0:17:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, don’t shake us, \Nthe handlebars are unsteady! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.96,0:17:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes straight ahead, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.13,0:17:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you... {/but...}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.68,0:18:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys is in the lead!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.88,0:18:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliant!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.63,0:18:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Gladys, you can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.46,0:18:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it, Gladys, keep it up!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.65,0:18:25.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I let her break away, \Nit’ll be all over. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.80,0:18:27.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must stick close...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.14,0:18:32.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,My body feels heavy…
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.85,0:18:34.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,my legs won’t lift any more.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.79,0:18:43.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,I mustn’t fall behind...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.16,0:18:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.15,0:18:55.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,No... I can’t run any longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.65,0:18:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys, don’t give in! \NYou must run right to the finish.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.64,0:19:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.81,0:19:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And your father in heaven is cheering too!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.51,0:19:07.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes… Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.12,0:19:14.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,Father, run with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.40,0:19:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.39,0:19:32.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Gladys, don’t push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.36,0:19:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Mum, sis is not leading!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.87,0:19:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There she is!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.72,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum, she's right there!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.16,0:19:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.40,0:20:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.70,0:20:05.97,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.81,0:20:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.41,0:20:09.44,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Ain't that great? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.44,0:20:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mother...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.18,0:20:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, Gladys has come third!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.85,0:20:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the dream of the Olympics is within reach.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.52,0:20:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cheering.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.22,0:20:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like, do come to my house. \NI should love to give you tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.03,0:20:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.31,0:20:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.39,0:20:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That tea cosy...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.40,0:20:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I made it from the scraps \Nyou gave Gladys. {it's mother speaking}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.52,0:20:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What lovely patchwork!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.44,0:20:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother is so clever with her hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.15,0:20:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I take after Father, so I’m no good.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.22,0:21:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead, you can run fast. \NYour father was a sprinter, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.99,0:21:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Had he not hurt his leg in an accident when young, \Nhe might have run in the Olympics himself. {i have to wonder if this episode was inspired by chariots of fire}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.95,0:21:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, I’ll go to the Olympics in his place!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.69,0:21:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it who called Gladys \Na poor, unfortunate girl?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.94,0:21:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We really had it all wrong, didn’t we?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.95,0:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladys’s family may have no father, \Nand they don’t live in luxury,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.20,0:21:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but don’t you think they live richly?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.40,0:21:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Warmly and happily, \Nwith hearts full of wealth. {lit: feels like their hearts are rich - literally "have a lot of money"}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.54,0:21:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She never needed our meddlesome charity at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.96,0:21:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and I feel a bit ashamed.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.25,0:22:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does all that power \Ncome from in such a slight body?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.35,0:22:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t help admiring her!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.96,0:22:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what about turning the Gladys Support Club\N into the Send Gladys to the Olympics Club?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.96,0:22:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds great, let’s!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.76,0:22:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But do promise not to say \Nwe must run with her every day!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.02,0:23:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On our history outing, we went to see \Nthe site linked with the legend of King Arthur.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.04,0:23:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ever so romantic, wasn’t it, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.36,0:23:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, for we lived through history itself \Nand met the gallant knight Sir Lancelot.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.29,0:23:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone may think it’s a tall story, \Nbut it’s the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.42,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely, isn’t it, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.00,0:23:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a dream, or an illusion?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.40,0:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Only we shall ever know!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.40,0:23:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.72,0:23:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"What! History Might be Changed?!" {あっ! 歴史が変っちゃう!?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.29,0:24:03.76,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 23 \NWhat! History Might be Changed?! {あっ! 歴史が変っちゃう!?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.71,0:24:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
